snippet.textDisplay:
As a Warfaze fan for 35 yrs, would have loved all the original creators of the song on screen. Russel vai Romel vai ke onek miss korlam. 
Would have been amazing if Romel vai played the legendary keyboard piece :( although loved Kamal Vai’s guiter rendition ☺️

Still a very good try, just Palash felt really out of place in the song. My personal opinion.

snippet.textDisplay:
That Babna sir,
The mythical voice.
The heart started to sing with the rythm of Remels wind and this song.
I returned to myself, which I have lost somany years ago.
It’s like,everything is moving beside and I am alone who is standing on the railing and getting goosebumps hearing these.
He has magic in his voice. 😭
Bro I'm crying.😭

But nothing can beat the old flutes tune.

snippet.textDisplay: This reminds me of the time 2007/8 when father used to play this song in his speaker and I used to listen to it and wonder how can a song's  lyrics and melody can totally be at harmony and sound so magical...It has been two years that my father has passed....but still it reminds me of him and my childhood in my old home.....a cup of tea in the evening with my whole family without any electricity....feels nostalgic

snippet.textDisplay:
This isn't just about the songs; it's about thousands of memories, and I still feel the same emotions. Thanks to Coke Studio for bringing back these memories and reminding me of how deeply music can move me. 

There's so much to say about this version, and I can't express enough gratitude to Coke Studio and Warfaze. You made this happen with Babna Karim, and his voice is still as surreal and powerful as ever. Palash Noor did an incredible job too; I can only imagine how challenging it must be to perform alongside the legend who originally wrote, sang, and composed the song. 

The atmosphere in the video was unbelievable. It felt like I was sitting by the seaside under a full moon, immersed in the music. I believe Babna Bhai felt the same. Thank you, Coke Studio, and best wishes for the future. I'm confident you'll continue to make us proud.
snippet.textOriginal:

You made this happen with Babna Karim, and his voice is still as surreal and powerful as ever. Palash Noor did an incredible job too; I can only imagine how challenging it must be to perform alongside the legend who originally wrote, sang, and composed the song. 

The atmosphere in the video was unbelievable. It felt like I was sitting by the seaside under a full moon, immersed in the music. I believe Babna Bhai felt the same. Thank you, Coke Studio, and best wishes for the future. I'm confident you'll continue to make us proud.
